OL,3,CThe collapse of Welsh rugby: From
OL,4,Cworld No.1 to 'laughing stock'
OL,6,FThe millions they received was used to
OL,7,Fcreate academies attached to each
OL,8,Fregion. It meant coaches, including
OL,9,Fthe likes of Aled Walters who would go
OL,10,Fon to win the World Cup with South
OL,11,FAfrica, were closely monitoring young
OL,12,Fplayers.
OL,14,FThe standards demanded were incredibly
OL,15,Fhigh and it produced a generation of
OL,16,Fplayers - that included Sam Warburton,
OL,17,FLeigh Halfpenny, Jonathan Davies, Dan
OL,18,FBiggar - who would go on to take Welsh
OL,19,Frugby to new heights.
